espond quickly. Cheers!\n\n70#Badge of Honor|Team, this month marks a time in our company's history: a linear TV/CTV and omni-channel brand campaign.  Bringing our company's first commercial to market has been quite the adventure.  Despite years of experience between us, none of us had ever brought an ad to market during a pandemic. We learned so much together. It has been joyful, difficult, fun, frustrating, and one of the best examples of resilience, trust, compassion, and teamwork I have seen,  At each and every step, you remained positive, committed, and determined to create something beautiful.  Thank you for all of your hard work.  Excited to see what comes next. I am so proud of you!\n\n71#Diving into the deep end...what, there's no water?|Water or no water, you dove in immediately, helped out big time with Havas and the commercial, and made a Huuuuuuuuge difference this week.  Your hard work, done quickly, across multiple teams was done with the highest quality.    Have a great weekend!\n\n72#Paving the way|Team, what a crazy whirlwind these past few weeks have been.  We are creating a foundation from which our brand push and investment in the funnel can realize gains in our brand health and valuation and our business outcomes unlike any we have seen before. It is such an honor to work alongside each of you as we work through our combined objectives, different investment mix models, and performance indicators that help us understand the impact of each and every dollar. Thank you for bringing your all to the table, for creating incredible relationships with our agencies, and by holding up a level of accountability that both inspires and ignites excitement for what is to come.\n\n73#Swoops in and saves the day|Carrie and John, in just a matter of minutes, you two assembled and created a dream team to get critical slides across the finish line in a matter of hours for Eric. Thank you so much for your attention to detail, to quality, to urgency, and to teamwork.