e have always had the best interests of Marketing and Workhuman in our mind.  Today was a big step.  Our promise to each other in early January was that we would build a plan that explained what we did, and do so with involvement from the entire team.  We did, and even added a few things over the past week while roles were shifting.  And I am so proud to see the cohesion across our plan, and the fun we have as human beings.  I am excited to see what we make happen in Q2 and the rest of the year.  Thank you, thank you for all you have done to get us to this point!  John\n\n78#Teamwork Truly Does Make Dreamwork|A huge thank you to each of your for a fantastic whirlwind of an update.  I am so grateful for your preparation and willingness to answer tough rapid fire questions (due to time constraints ;-)).  This team is the backbone of the marketing organization. Your dedication to creating an agile digital marketing infrastructure designed for scale and growth, all the while doing your BAU, is awe-inspiring. THANK YOU for always keeping a sense of humor and your commitment to our team and our company. ONWARD.\n\n79#Team Value Creation|Much overdue, but so very deserving, is this recognition to this collective team of magicians who took a rudimentary, half-baked, error-riddled spreadsheet and turned it into a powerfully compelling secret weapon in the war for a more human workplace.      On behalf of my colleague Rob, the senior leaders who supported the concept and vision for the calculator, and all the sales reps who stand close lots of deals . . .  we all would like to express our deepest gratitude to this amazing set of teammates who came together to turn our vision into something so magical, so compelling, and so valuable for prospects who want to understand in hard $'s the impact our solution can have on their business results when considering an investment in the Workhuman Cloud.     John, your early understanding of our vision and ability to identify and procure 