elp run the slide show. This isn't the first time you've helped me with my tech woes and I suspect, it won't be the last. Thank you for being a great teammate and friend.\n\n82#Lights! Camera! ACTION!!|A great big long overdue thank you for all of the amazing work that was put into creating the GE - 17 yr partnership video! We will be sharing this with all GE stakeholders as part of our strategic marketing outreach campaign to win the RFP this year! Thank you to the video team for the long hours of editing and fine tuning. (sorry about all of the changes :/ ) And a big shout out to our amazing speakers who all submitted a lengthy list of \"takes\" necessary to provide the selection of content needed to put this together. And a special thank you to Christina, who diligently kept us ON point and ON schedule during a very busy time for all of us. The video came out great! Thanks for your contributions!!\n\n83#Problem Solving|Thanks so much for popping on a quick call this week to brainstorm how to iterate and improve the customer newsletter process and content. Diaries are jam-packed with lots of projects in the air. So greatly appreciate the time taken to hear viewpoints, ideate and discuss feedback in a super productive way! I think we landed in a good spot and excited for the future. Cheers to this great team!\n\n84#Yes Sir, can I help some more!|John, you have been a mountain of support for me over the past month, learning how we do things and guiding on new, better ways.  And you jumped in to help Sam, support Dianne and so much more, and always willing to do so on a moments notice.  You are always willing to do some more!\n\n85#Workfront guru to the rescue|John, thank you for helping me bring the integrated calendar back to life in Workfront. It‚Äôs becoming more and more important to capture all the great work that is happening live and this is just a start of what it will look like to share what‚Äôs going on cross functionally to allow teams to leverage each other‚Äôs work or simple provide awareness. I appreciate your endless excitement to find ways to make the tool work better for us!\n\n86#Marketer or Marketeer?|No matter which way you market yourself, Amy and I wanted to thank this entire team for the investment over the last few weeks, leading up to today - our first integrated planning offsite of 2021! You invested your time, energy, mind and heart in the offsite topics and each other. We appreciate the opportunity for transparency, communication and idea sharing around two of our most important upcoming initiatives between the Brand Relaunch and WH Live. We're both excited to be aligned, looking forward to building out integrated marketing plans together, and thrilled to be on this journey with each of you. Onward we go! Z & Amy\n\n87#Presentation Powerhouse|On behalf of Rosette and myself, we want to thank you for jumping in at the 11th hour  to help Rosette prepare for her HRO Today Performance Management Session. While we may have been looking for design assistance at a late hour, you were able to problem solve in real time, provide slide options that fit the story, and give Rosette the support she needed to make it all come together. We appreciate your efforts and brain power in making this happen!\n\n88#Pioneer Squad|Thanks all for either being the first few people to complete and submit the speaking engagements request form in Workfront or for joining one of our first two speakers bureau office hours. Our hope is that the new process is both simple and useful to all areas of the business. You've helped to kick it all off by jumping in without hesitation and asking all the right questions. We look forward to your feedback as we continue throughout the year!\n\n89#Now that's how you lead!|Sam, John and Mark, Your leadership and organization came through loud and clear today on the Directors' Call.  We have a plan to make Martech Wow our customers, and to lead projects that drive exceptional value to Workhuman. 