th the potential to change the landscape for Workhuman!  Please pass this gratitude along to anyone not the list, or potentially outside of our org (thinking of our freelancers who have been called on to elevate their work to ensure best-in-class messaging)!  Cheers, all!\n\n100#Lights, Camera, Action Groups!|Team - Z and I want to thank you all for your work getting the Pulse Survey Action Groups kicked off. Your ideas we so thoughtful and well crafted for the short window we gave you. We are beyond impressed! As Chris said, this is hugely important work and it is ongoing. We are excited to continue our partnership with you as we build and develop out these programs! We are grateful for you all!\n\n101#Speaking Engagments Form|John, thanks for taking the lead on creating the speaking engagments request form in Workfront. This will allow Amanda and I to track requests and engagment details like topic areas and audience size/levels in a more consistent manner. Thanks for taking the time to walk through the process to ensure it‚Äôs simple but aligned to our reporting needs.\n\n102#Quick turn request|Thank you all for your collaboration and focus on a quick turn request to create an overview doc to support C suite outreach. Ilana for your messaging suggestions, John and Dianne for getting it kicked-off and keeping it on track, Lauren for your quick copy writing, and Carrie for bringing it over the finish line with great layout and design. Thank you!\n\n103#The Workhuman brand experience|A brand is an alchemy of identity, emotion, experiences, charisma ‚Äì the soul of the company and the products it makes. Remove any of these factors you‚Äôre left looking at only part of the picture. Unless you look at how people interact with a company and its products, you don‚Äôt have a holistic picture of the brand. The experience is cohesive and purposeful though brand identity, marketing communications, physical environments and product experiences. I'm so grateful to partner with