ies, a product launch, a computer that wouldn't start up, and so many other things ahead of this event that could've derailed the demo but nothing stopped this team. I appreciate all the work you all put into making this a great event for our customers. It went off without a hitch and I can't thank you all enough for your help! Thank you, thank you, thank you!\n\n107#Have a Minute? ... And Much More|When I was approached with pulling together a plan and resources for a short-form video series to provide education on ‚Äúwho we are and what we do,‚Äù each of you stepped up in a big way to make it happen. The ‚ÄúHave a Minute‚Äù video series showcases different Workhuman themes that not only educate, but humanize our brand. From simply answering the question, ‚ÄúWho is Workhuman?,‚Äù to articulating why the annual review is not enough, to discussing the differences between employee engagement and employee experience, to promoting the new book, Live Online, and Workhuman Certified ‚Äì ‚ÄúHave a Minute?‚Äù has provided a punchy, quick lens into our business through our humans. Whether you have been behind the scenes with video, script writing or reporting, in front of the camera, or hosting the series (that‚Äôs you, Patti), I appreciate the time, energy, and focus you bring to the program. We‚Äôve learned a lot from this approach, and have some excellent ideas in the queue for making this bigger and better. Thanks for contributing to our mission to make work more human for every person around the globe.\n\n108#Are the forefront of Workfront|Hey John. Recently I was getting very frustrated trying to navigate and be productive using workfront. It's a very complicated tool that has many capabilities but isn't always easy to find the right thing you need. It also doesn't help that I was working in an old version and didn't know it. You took the time to reengage my dashboard and walk me through some newer and more efficient views. Thank you for your help and helping me work better!\n\n109#Congrats Workhuman Live Team!|Team ‚Äì A HUGE shout out to each of you for helping deliver a fantastic event yesterday. It truly was amazing! Your hard work and dedication to excellence have set a NEW example for everyone in our organization. I‚Äôm inspired by the ingenuity and creativity of everyone‚Äôs contribution ‚Äì planning, marketing, storytelling, vendor management, customer support, technical execution, and so much more. Your efforts have allowed us to create a new conversation in the marketplace. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to help every organization bring people closer together. None of this would be possible without YOU. I extend my heartiest congratulations on achieving a fantastic milestone. Well done ALL!\n\n110#GTM elevated to a new standard|Team, to say I am proud of each and every one of you for the work you did to bring Certified to market - well,  it would be an understatement.  In bringing this program to market, your commitment to success, to each other, and to our customers was visible. You drove never-before practiced approaches including taking integrated launch to a whole new level of collaboration and stakeholder management, you delivered incredible market research, a beautiful web experience, and so much more.  Congratulations to you.   I will miss our 8 am's!\n\n111#I see you|John, Dianne, Angela, Brian, and Christina - I just want you to know that I see how hard you are working every day to keep hundreds of parts moving on hundreds of different projects. Not only are you doing this during a major crunch time for everyone with the impending broadcast of Workhuman Live Online next week, but all of you are also working toward earning your PMP certification in addition to everything else on your plates. I appreciate the staggering breadth of what you do for this team - and particularly as it relates to my projects. I am in back and forth communication with each of you on a regular basis and I know 