ery much for helping take my boring Powerpoint and helping update it to the next level. The changes make a big difference that help to capture, and tell, an important story. Thank you!\n\n116#Virtual Offsite - but 100% Productive IRL|Team - On behalf of Patti and myself thank you for a tremendous Q3 strategic planning and execution offsite last week. Both presenters and discussion partners excelled in their roles to communicate and strengthen existing plans. Your engagement and participation was locked in for the full session. And it's exciting to see this team rally around a new way of working that is oriented toward connecting business results to the strategic objectives of all our 2H initiatives within Marketing and across partner stakeholder teams. Thanks for leaning into the process - it's becoming a difference maker for us and helping us cut through our own noise! -C\n\n117#Taking the reigns|John, thank you for your involvement in the heavy lifting the team has done to get the October event   stood up. You tirelessly come back to the basics again and again so the various groups and individuals of the larger team don't stray off course. You words and your work matter. Keep it up. Cheers!\n\n118#The PM Santa Claus of Christmas in July|John, thank you for taking time out of your Sunday to not only print out the massive amount of materials needed to prepare for the PMP (the box is about as heavy as a cinder block), but also personally delivering them to the each member of the Project Management team. This along with your support in getting the necessary online training gives us a great head start on our preparation for this notoriously difficult exam. It was also a great chance to see you and meet Leia, if only for a few minutes (while practicing proper social distancing techniques)!\n\n119#Keeping us aligned!|Team, thank you so much for all your support and excellent project management since we have been WFH. I have had the opportunity to work with each of you in