epresents an important evolution in many respects.  Your teamwork with each other and with your stakeholders is exactly how we collectively transform our brand trajectory.  Thank you!  Patti\n\n124#Putting the \"Lift off\" in \"Kick off\"|Team - as workplaces everywhere contemplate the next phase of work, we are leading the way in what that looks like externally and with our customers. It also means we need to evolve internally. I was so impressed by the team work and open mindedness demonstrated by this cross-functional group in today's kick off! So, as they say, \"Houston, we have lift off!\" Excited to see where this group takes the next phase of what it means to thrive and workhuman. With gratitude, -C\n\n125#What Makes Us Human: Heart and Soul|Team, when most of us are feeling defeated, deflated, and hopeless, each of you came together to unite our hearts and souls with the people we most want to reach. I shed more than one tear experiencing the imagery and messages of hope and pragmatism. Your respect, empathy, and compassion for all hearts and souls inside and outside of our company has made an impact.  Thank you for transforming a sad exception to our lives into one that brings us together instead of dividing us all.  As always, thank you for your hard work and determination to Workhuman. Best, Patti\n\n126#Crash course on getting to know you|John - I just want to say I've really enjoyed my crash course on getting to know you this week. When I came back from leave in the summer of last year, I didn't get to work with you much at first but throughout our interactions talking about process, excel templates, calendars, and being desk/row neighbors, I was able to get to know you on a personal level and I really do see you for the compassionate and driven leader you are. Fast-forward to this week, and I've finally had the pleasure of getting to work with you on the BLM campaign which has been such a delight! Things are moving fast, but your communication style is