e confronted with the fierce urgency of now. In this unfolding conundrum of life and history, there IS such a thing as being too late. This is not time for apathy or complacency. This is a time for vigorous and positive action.\" - MLK JR.   Team, since I started just over a month ago, I have heard from many of you and our stakeholders who have talked about the misfortune of joining Workhuman during a global pandemic that has changed every thing about how we live: from how we interact, to what we spend our time and money on, what we value, and how we work.  The truth is, there was no better time for me to be able to witness the magic that is Workhuman. We already know what is important and that is human connection. What you have demonstrated is humanity during a time of extreme urgency - a rarity in life and certainly in business. Thank you for your passion for your and your commitment to each other and our stakeholders.  I am honored to work alongside each of you.\n\n131#Project Management‚Äôs Obi-Wan Kenobi|The past couple of weeks have been among the busiest I‚Äôve encountered while at Workhuman, but there have been several moments during that time that have once again demonstrated to me what an amazing privilege it is having you as the leader of our PM team. You always have our back, available to discuss any issue or opportunity that arises, provide advice or just keeping us laughing in our morning ‚Äúface-to-face‚Äù team meetings. At the start of the Moodtracker go-to-market campaign you helped set up a new Agile way of working in Workfront, focused on the excitement of the opportunity rather how daunting the road ahead was. This new agile approach guided our daily sprints and provided a visual representation of the progress the team was making. Throughout the entire campaign I never doubted I had your support, and you didn‚Äôt hesitate to jump in whenever an assist when needed. You truly are the Jedi Master of Project Management, an amazing leader and a great friend. Thank you!\n\n132#Rock solid PM team!|Team, You have been in major communication with our Marketing teams organizing huge campaigns for the company over the past several weeks. You haven‚Äôt taken a day off or taken part in all the self care activities happening. You worked extra hours to pull off some amazing things, managing every detail along the way. There have never been so many big initiatives launching at the same time and making such a huge impact in the company and the world at a time like this. Who knew 2020 was going to the year for Workhuman to take it beyond the next level! I just wanted to take a moment to recognize you for all your hard work and achievements that are coming to fruition over the next week+ for Livestream, Moodtracker, CSR and more! You let me lean on you to take the big dogs, while I‚Äôve been helping to keep the smaller projects moving. This has allowed me to maintain my sanity while parenting solo, teaching, and working. I‚Äôm so proud to have you by my side proving the strengths of project management in everything you do! Thank you for being strong teammates especially when I needed you the most.\n\n133#Synchronizing our Story|The biggest of creative and project management shout outs to this team of inspirational teammates! We have a big opportunity with a customer this week to tell our story. I reached out to the world (to a LOT of people---my bad) and the world sent me back this fine group! Your creativity and design is EXACTLY what we needed and you really WOW'd me with how beautifully and quickly delivered. I recognize how many competing priorities everyone is balancing and it means SO much that you could help me help the team. MERCI BEAUCOUP! You're brilliant!\n\n134#All systems go!|This group rallied mid week in an incredible pivot from soft launch to just LAUNCH within hours. I cannot thank you enough for the commitment to urgency for launching media campaigns.\n\n135#Thank You Healthcare Images - Weekend Worriors|Thank you all for jumping in to take part in the logo and image sourcing and uploading for hospitals into the Thank You Healthcare site!  Ensuring that the experience is personal and meaningful for those who access the site is incredibly important and your help in making this happen was invaluable! I got to see first-hand your passion, collaboration and sheer energy brought to this exciting task!  You gave up time over your Easter weekend with family to dedicate energy toward this grand human cause.  Adam, Becky and Meghan, thank you for leading the cross functional team from activating help from across the company, providing detailed instructions (that even I could follow), guidance, direction, answering questions and providing top tips and learnings throughout the process, even participating as heavy hitters in the uploading and sourcing as well! When I asked you, Becky and Meg, to help partner with Adam and the technology team to make this happen you were so excited to be a part of this phenomenal project and your pride was palpable- thank you!  You guys have become the 3 amigos!  Superb effort, and excellent management, your incredible knowledge and attention to detail has been awe-inspiring! Thank you also to each of you who dedicated an hour, several hours and in some cases most of the weekend to sourcing and uploading!  We so appreciate your efforts!  Many hands make light work, my mother used to say! I do want to call out a few of you who really made an incredible dent in the project uploading and sourcing between 70 and 230 images each and in many cases hitting both uploading and sourcing!  WOW!  Brian Moore, Matt Durgin, John Wamback, Jon Bizeur, Amanda Salvas, Rich Sorrentino, Jillian Gregoriou and Dan Fiore, you guys are complete rock stars and your contributions were mammoth! This was a true team effort and to see it in action makes me so proud to be a part of our Workhuman family!  Amazing job! Let‚Äôs share some gratitude with the world now!\n\n136#Check