s yesterday afternoon. This was both a great initiative to showcase our respect for our customers and all members in the healthcare industry, as well as such a great team collaboration. Each and every one of you played a crucial part in making this so successful.   I was personally excited and touched by this video since I have so many family members and close friends in the front lines, and I'm so excited to share with them to brighten their day!\n\n144#Delivering the Human Touch|When the COVID-19 pandemic began to accelerate, our marketing instinct immediately went to providing a human face on our content. There is no more powerful thought leadership than humans speaking with humans ‚Äì sharing experiences, emotions, and best practices on how best to craft a path forward in these unprecedented times. That was the inspiration for the daily video series, ‚ÄúKeeping Work Human,‚Äù which launched last week amid the flurry of everything else we are working on. James and Matt ‚Äì you stepped up and deftly handled the logistics of turning a Zoom video conference call into usable, shareable video. Pam ‚Äì you project-managed the overall logistics, setting up the invites, and showing agility when we had to pivot. Amy ‚Äì you immediately energized your team to schedule guest speakers. Mike ‚Äì you were at the ready to transition the videos to Workhuman Radio podcasts. Sarah and Jess ‚Äì you stepped up to write the question frameworks and provide a content resource. John and Diane ‚Äì you saw what was happening and introduced better discipline and process. Jen ‚Äì you were our first guest and dazzled our viewers with unique leadership best practices to manage remote teams. And Steve ‚Äì our host ‚Äì your ability to set the tone, and keep our guests at ease with your authenticity and humble heart, is what makes it all work. We‚Äôve only just begun ‚Äì and we have a busy few weeks ahead ‚Äì but I couldn‚Äôt be prouder of this team and the messaging we are bringing to market.\n\n145#Leaning on the Experts|Guys, I really appreciate your support over the last few days as we worked through the details of the video series. Thank you for sharing your input on how this should work, look, and be delivered to the audience. We‚Äôre moving so fast and making decisions quickly, and doing that well is only possible when we trust the team around us. I‚Äôm extremely grateful to each of you for sharing your expertise!\n\n146#The Daily French Digest!|Team, A huge thank you for your quick work and endless pivoting on the construct of the daily existing customer email communications. Alice, Eileen, Traci, Chris and Kevin, wordsmith-ing at its finest! You worked super hard to get this first intro email to a great place and really helpful leadership direction and vision! John, I don't know what we would do without your stellar PM skillz! Lauren and Moe, quick turns on the brainstorms and thank you for the light hearted moments when I needed them most! Jess and Meghan, your help on list building, direction and ensuring our reporting is in line - so important! And finally, Anthony, thank you for burning the midnight oil with me. What I asked of you wasn't super 'Workhuman' and I cannot thank you enough for juggling what you did to get the communication out! Thank you all for your commitment to this project!\n\n147#Sharing is caring|High 5s to you 5 fine humans! Why you ask? I pulled together a marketplace update over the weekend but with more than a dozen companies to track, I knew I could not do it alone. I asked the marketing leaders who could help out and Dan and John - you both didn't blink raising your hand to chip in. Dan - your team is cranking out thoughtful content every day but you generously offered to let Jess H help with this. John - first you said you could ask your team to help but then you decided to take on the extra workload yourself! Jess - you were quick, thorough and proactively reached out to me with your specific updates throughout the week. But, as the week went on and our COVID related scope of work kept growing, I knew I had to reassess how we resourced the efforts so that we could provide timely updates to Sales and the entire organization. Pam - I went to you next and asked if I could enlist Mark's help. And you too, didn't hesitate a second. You quickly talked to Mark and followed up to tell me he'd be in touch. Within hours, Mark not only proactively reached out to me for the download but he took the project on with ease and enthusiasm and delivered a new update of today's marketplace COVID related activity Hugely valuable. Thank you all! I love this team and this great example of teamwork at its finest.\n\n148#Everyone needs a rock...I've got a few!|Over the past few days, we've been working more closely together than ever before. Things are moving at a rapid pace, there's a constant fire hose of new ideas and projects, changing direction....plus the shared learning curve of how to be the most productive yet communicative and inclusive while we all embrace working remotely. It's been a roller coaster ride of emotions and I wanted you to know how grateful I am to be on this ride with you two. Thank you for being excellent strategic partners. In more ways than one, you've kept me sane - well, SOMEWHAT sane. ;-)\n\n149#Quick strike team|Hi all - thank you for your tireless collaboration today on all of the different email communications that we're putting out into the world. You've each been wonderful to work with - Jill and Z, providing clarity of direction; Lauren being quick with all the words; John, keeping the tasks organized and all of us on track... Great teamwork, respect for urgency and respect for quality all around. I love that amidst uncertainty - we can still shine! (yep, that was cheesy and i don't care)\n\n150#Be the glue|At then end of a very long 2 days of a long week in a stressful time... thank you for taking a few minutes to talk to me this afternoon. Your calm manner is valuable. Thank you for being a listening manager. Continue to be glue that holds us together as a marketing department.\n\n151#It's Go Time!|Team - I wanted to first say thank you for your rapid response to the business's need for a COVID rapid response campaign. I also want to acknowledge that working at this pace and with a level of uncertainty may be new and/or uncomfortable, but that has not stopped this group from leaping into action, mobilizing, and being agile and responsive to rapidly evolving priorities - including stopping existing work, pivoting planned content, and being open-minded about new ways of working team together and team apart (as we leverage remote technology for the next while). Still lots to do, and I'm confident with the cohesion demonstrated this week we will do great things that help our current and future customers navigate uncertain times and that we will unlock new approaches and agility as a cross functional team. Thank you all. With gratitude, -C\n\n152#Team Corona|Coronavirus.  Covid-19.  A giant headache.  We all call it something different ‚Äì especially because the situation with it has been changing minute by minute and making our decision making process so challenging.  When we made the decision to create new content and FAQ‚Äôs for our Workhuman Live site and audiences at 8PM on a Friday night, I crossed my fingers we would be able to activate.  We needed to get information out to our audiences that was clear, consistent, and valuable to ensure they felt informed and at ease.  No surprise ‚Äì every single one of you stepped up.  Dianne was slacking me almost immediately with project set-up details and timelines.  Lauren had copy in my hands before 6:00 AM (you actually sent it at 1:30!?!)  Chris and Amy were both there to review, edit and get on the phone to talk it through.  Jon had site pages staged and new pop-up functionality built and staged Saturday morning.  Jen and Anthony had layouts and content ready to deploy.  Jill was providing copy strategy and reviews.  Holly and Anne were standing by ready to act as needed for our audiences.  And Lauren ‚Äì our guiding light and champion of strategy supporting the whole process was as responsive as ever with reviews and feedback.  This is such an evolving and fluid situation, but the team never ceases to amaze me.  You gave up family and weekend time to help ensure our customers had the information they needed, when they needed it.  Your continued dedication and respect for customers, urgency, quality, and teamwork is amazing.  Thank you ‚Äì and Cheers to Team Corona.\n\n153#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n154#Easy as pie|John, you have a way about you that makes everything you‚Äôre working on seem as easy as pie. There have been some small things here and there that needed some fixin‚Äô! You tackled a bunch of things for me and the team over the past week and I wanted to let you know how much I appreciated your attention to all these details. Setting up a PM team meeting to make sure we are all setting up projects consistently, working on new dashboards to display our request queue, fixing the proofing issue, and endless training meetings to rollout the new ways of working as well as Workfront training to teams outside of Marketing. Thanks for all your support and positive attitude!\n\n155#Making work(flow) human|John, Brian, Angela, Dianne, Christina, and Michael - I have to give your team a shout out for all the communicating you do around projects and schedules on a constant basis. And especially for my own schedule, to have such a caring group of humans always having an eye on my workload is a godsend. This week especially, each of you has done something to shift deadlines in a way that's made my work manageable. Each of you has asked me on multiple occasions if I am okay and what can you do to help. I can't tell you how much I appreciate all of you, your devotion to keeping workflow efficient and human, and the sense of positivity and calm you bring to our department. You're helping all of us do our best work and that's deserving of all the praise in the world.\n\n156#Thank you / Thank Gu|Daisy, Dana, Genessa, Jen, John, Kristen, Mary, Sara & Vahagn - thank you all for you support sending follow up note to the sales team following Ignite. It was great to have this team lend creativity to help us send a thoughtful note, along with some Gu, to the team. Thank you - or I should say thank Gu.\n\n157#Diplomacy at its best|John I wanted to recognize you for the outstanding presentation you gave to the marketing group today, as you walked us through the big vision regarding our new ways of working. The basics were presented in a digestible way, and with your trademark friendly and matter-of-fact tone. You made everyone feel included and heard, which set the room at ease - a very challenging thing to do with our group! I think we all realize that this is the first step of many, as we go forward, but I was so reassured walking out of there that you and the project management team will help us get where we all want to go.\n\n158#Ignite photography|John, Thank you for your help securing the photographer to capture the activities at Ignite Boston. It was a long shot list and I‚Äôm looking forward to seeing everything and sharing with employees. Really appreciate your help finding the person and sorting all that out in advance and your help with the activities on site too.\n\n159#A Good Night with a Few Good Men...|Amidst the blur of the pace of life, it is always nice to slow life down for a bit and connect about the ties that bind and the moments that really matter-and in the process learn something that you would not have otherwise known. Thank you for the honor and privilege of your company and for the camaraderie that will not end just because our dinner did.\n\n160#Enriching the SLC experience for winners|Colleen and John, thank you both for your help in creating a great experience for all of this year's Sales Leadership Club nominees.  Arranging for photos to be captured in the moment, combing through them all to pick suitable one's right away, editing/advising/enhancing other elements of the messaging and helping identify the best way to make the awards real.  And when we hit minor bumps in the road - John with the mystery of the missing photo and Colleen with the impromptu use of your own phone - you each stepped in right away to help. Thank you for being such great collaborators.\n\n161#Lights! Camera! It's the final countdown!|John, I truly appreciate all the work you did securing our photographer for the corporate headshots from beginning to end. Glenn was a huge hit with everyone who interacted with him, and I'm so excited to see the end result. What I'm most proud of is the way you helped get the last slideshow of the event up before the curtain closed! What a close call, but you did it and it was the perfect way to close out our Ignite. Thanks for being such an incredible team player.\n\n162#Being Human|One of my favorite parts of our yearly Ignite program is the dine arounds. It‚Äôs a chance to spend time with our fellow humans in an informal setting, with no rush, no pressure, just humans connecting. Last night, this paid off in spades. I want to say a heartfelt ‚Äúthank you‚Äù to each one of you for being your authentic self! I loved the free-flowing conversations we had, the opportunity to learn more about each one of you, to share our similarities, and to find out what makes each of us unique. It‚Äôs experiences like this that make me proud to work with all of you at Workhuman.\n\n163#Efficiencies give me LIFE!|I want to THANK YOU for taking time to meet and brainstorm on assets to incorporate into the Project Management process. It has been great partnering with you and experiencing how you ALWAYS keep an open mind and value opinions/feedback.  It's a breath of fresh air and I am so excited to be a part of the PM team and the great things our team is going to do in 2020!\n\n164#New form, who dis?|John, my first time working directly with you has been such a delight. Thank you for your openness and responsiveness to helping the comms team centralize any and all speaking asks. Within one day you were showing us a newly created form on Workfront, which for the time being will allow us to report more easily and accurately on all internal and external engagements.  I look forward to working with you more this year.\n\n165#Go team!|John, you assembled this team faster than the avengers, and every bit as strong. Your expertise in this area has already helped drive so much positive change - thank you for trailblazing. Angela and Dianne, you have achieved Ol'G status - thank you for all you've both done for the team in your time here and have shown tremendous leadership in onboarding everyone else. Brian, its never a simple task to shift your focus area, it takes a lot of courage and hard work to do this, and you do it with kindness and positivity. Michael and Christina, you both have been here for like, a month or less - and already I'm so impressed at the focus, energy, and expertise you bring to projects & discussions. 2020 is shaping up to be a great year!\n\n166#Wamback has our backs|John, I want to thank you for your tireless efforts around putting the right processes and workflows in place to make it easier to do our best work. Since you‚Äôve been here, you‚Äôve taken huge steps to improve the way we work together, to shed light on what‚Äôs necessity and what‚Äôs self-imposed, and to ease the burden of those who are over-scheduled. You‚Äôre slowly but surely turning the chaos into calm, and I so appreciate you for this. Not to mention, your understanding and empathy. You always come at everything with a compassionate ear and a solutions-driven mind. So glad you‚Äôre here. We needed you.\n\n167#Dream Team!|John, Thank you for planning and leading our first team offsite last week. You have project management skills after all ;-) It was great to step away from projects to talk about our job and how we can best support our teammates in marketing and beyond. It was helpful to see all the presentations you've developed to clarify our roles. It is so great to have a team and other PM brains to hang out with. Cheers!\n\n168#Merck Email test.... and we're live!|Thank you to this all-star team for your incredible contributions in getting our first Redemption Reminder email test live!!  As a small but mighty team, you guys persevered through unchartered territory, navigating so many unknowns, obstacles, setbacks and changes, and ultimately got this first test live and out to the Merck US population (during peak holiday season no less, which is a huge window to impact!)  Now, not only do we have a sparkly new templates, processes and testing methodology to build on, but we also have AMAZING early results to start diving in to (hello 30% open rate on Day 1!) to learn more about how we can leverage the Email Channel to improve the customer experience and achieve our collective business goals.  Looking forward to continuing to partner with this group as we build out this 