sitive things to say about your conversations, and that is so important in attracting top talent!  YAY to 2 closed searches.  John, you are a great recruiting partner!\n\n172#Workfront in a hurry|Thank you SO much for making the Workfront html proof tool work on my machine!!! Being able to click through a website and make edits within the proofing tool is just magical ‚Äì¬†and I was in a hurry between meetings to get my edits to the team so we wouldn't lose time on the project (because when am I NOT rushing between meetings!). You were able to figure out how to make it work and update my proofing tool without needing to put in an IT ticket ‚Äì¬†and I am SO grateful! I would have lost an entire day on this project if I didn't have this tool working properly on my computer at just that time !!! thank you!\n\n173#Uncovered Company-Wide Tech Issue|Hi John,  From my first day here you equipped me with Workfront, only to have the \"Ground Hog Day\" effect where we needed to setup my account new each day! After digging deeper and working back and forth between Workfront and IT, you were instrumental in discovering the Single Sign On company-wide issue. Great patience and determination to get me (and others!) equipped to do our jobs!\n\n174#Kicking of Friday AM with some PM Inspiration|John - Thanks for a great project management brainstorming discussion this morning. I am really impressed with not only the ideas you are bringing to the table, but also the open dialogue you continue to have with Angela, Dianne and I. I'm very happy and excited to be part of this group, and can't wait to see what we can accomplish when we team up with the rest of Marketing and beyond. It was the perfect way to kick off a Friday and wrap up a productive week...I owe you some more gold coins!\n\n175#Successful Kick-off|John - thank you so much for recently taking the time to kick off your 2 newest Project Manager searches!  I'm so excited to be hiring for your team.  I loved working with you during your own hiring process, and things have come full circle.  This was the first time I kicked off our new job intake process.  Thank you for coming to the meeting so prepared, and for all of the information you shared with me.  I am confident in the hiring process we identified, and cannot wait to hit the ground running on this search!\n\n176#Thank you for the warm welcome!!|I meant to send this earlier this week, but I am still new to the system so apologies there! I finally found you though, and just want to send a big THANK YOU for the warm welcome and lunch earlier this week.  It was great to get some advice from you, and have you show me the way to the cafe next door. The small things make all of the difference, and you are part of the reason why it was such a great first week! THANK YOU!!!!!\n\n177#A new approach|After meeting with the three of you this week, I'm so excited of what's to come for our Benefits communications! I walked away from our meeting feeling inspired about the work we'll do together. I very much appreciate you all moving beyond the traditional and really helping me to think outside the box and push us further with this project (I can't wait to see the next version!).  As I review all the behaviors associated with Cultivating Innovation, the three of you displayed every single one in our meeting this week. Thank you for being great partners and approaching this project with positivity and creativity!\n\n178#Philips Demo Video|Hi Team, I just want to thank you for all your hard work in putting together the semi-custom video demo for our Philips pitch this week.  Jess, as always without hesitation you jumped right in to bring your creative ideas to help us think outside the box.  John, appreciate you running point on helping to orchestrate this along with the other projects the team had to make sure we had something in time to review, tweak and finalize before our pitch. Dan, thanks for the quick turnaround on incorporating their specific values into the site.  And James, thanks for giving the Workhuman solution a voice.  You collaborated with Marcy and I on the script so we could ensure we incorporated things like right to left languages, Workday, and multiple programs and you jumped right in to help us come up with a solution that could meet our timelines, but still make it a tailored experience.  Thank you - it made a tremendous impact day of and we will continue to use it going forward as we hopefully move into the next round of discussions.\n\n179#Grateful for your guidance|There was a moment yesterday where I was caught in the middle of a judgement call that had to be made. You got on the phone with me first thing in the morning to walk through the issue and help sort it out. There‚Äôs no way to please everyone, but you have a way of speaking to people that makes them feel respected and valued. You‚Äôve been such a great mentor in your short time here offering solid advice and always making us feel supported. I‚Äôm grateful for everything you‚Äôve done so far for our team. You have been a true advocate since day one.\n\n180#\"Clear is Kind\"|(Brene Brown) John - As you continue to champion the Project Management role, develop plans, and build a team of excellence - you often gather us to share the updates and ask for our input. This recognition is to thank you for the transparency. It allows us to walk the path with you, to feel a part of the plan, manages our expectations, and prevents a grapevine from growing. Way to lead and model collaboration!\n\n181#Desk dropping sparkles|Brian, Geoff, Niamh, Sara, Laury, Maureen, Austin and John ‚ÄîThank you all for jumping in to help us add some magic into the office! Many hands made way less work (and time), especially when it comes to untangling lights (John takes the cake on this one- light extraordinaire). Thank you for staying late, for your respect for urgency (and teamwork), and for making this fun. I appreciate you all!\n\n182#Just a great human|John, just wanted to take a moment to recognize how thoughtful and kind you are. There has been a lot of change and you have approached each conversation, some confidential in nature, with respect and dignity. And looking out for the other humans has been so refreshing to see. Keep on being just a great human.\n\n183#Truly Imagination at Work!|Let me start by saying how grateful I am for this entire team for the collaborative efforts that you all put forth to design & deliver the gorgeous GE demo prototype to 25+ leaders at GE this week.  The feedback that I got from GE was \"the custom demo really made the difference\" and from a senior healthcare leader, \"really interesting & exciting...how do we get started!!\"  That is amazing feedback!  Special thanks to the marketing team for all of your hard work and creativity put into the custom demo AND the custom micro-sites that we are building together. To Dan Fiore who we refused to allow to enjoy his vacation :), to Sarah Whitman for attending and presenting at the meeting even though we only gave you 5 min to speak!  And of course to my relentless team, Traci, Kara, and Meghan...you are simply amazing at what you do. One more hurdle at GE behind us. We are getting there, team!!\n\n184#Q4 style guide - Hello Gorgeous!|We asked, you delivered!  Maureen, John - thank you for your incredible work getting us to a place of reviewing a comprehensive style guide for Q4/holiday, and not to mention in August!  I'm blown away by the organization, the research and the visually stunning mood boards that you've pulled together to conceptualize what our holiday promotional strategy will look and feel like this year!  I think what you presented is spot for the Store brand we are all trying to build, and I couldn't be more excited to see our holiday campaign officially kick off!!  Thank you!!\n\n185#Let's do this thing.|TEAM! Super inspired after our meeting yesterday. I love where this is going and am appreciative of all the hard work, thought, preparation and leadership in completely changing the way we are approaching this company-wide initiative. I'm excited to be involved and be a part of something so much bigger than just one project or one department. Way to innovate and lead the charge. Times are a changin' and I am HERE for it!! Well done! #gratitag\n\n186#Roses are red....|Violets are blue. The Healthcare campaign would be nothing without you. I truly appreciate the teamwork, energy and dedication that went into getting these healthcare ads back in market. A lot of back and forth, and lots of collaboration toward a share goal. Many thanks. I'm excited to see what the market has to say and start iterating on the awesome creative and copy!\n\n187#In good hands|Thank you both for your support on my projects while I was on vacation. I know you have a stack of projects of your own to keep up with, but I left feeling confident all of my projects would be in good hands. What a relief! What a team!\n\n188#The Gratitude Effect|I am SO excited about where we are headed for our Gratitude Effect campaign. As a core team, we are learning what hasn‚Äôt worked and trying our new improved approach for this one. We are off to such a strong, strategic and efficient approach, I can‚Äôt wait to reveal it with the larger team tomorrow. In true test and learn fashion, let‚Äôs see if it works but even if it doesn‚Äôt, you were all so willing and open to trying, what more could I ask for? I‚Äôm so grateful for you!\n\n189#Doctor Workfront!|John - Thank you for the multiple project management working sessions over the past few weeks. I really appreciate your willingness to discuss how we as project managers can better serve our customers within Marketing and across the organization, while helping support our teammates so they can be the best creatives and content creators that they can be. You've also helped me really up my Workfront game, a process I hope will continue throughout 2019!\n\n190#Summertime!