pping us up. I want to thank my team for all of the great discussions we‚Äôve had thus far to make Improvements across the board. I‚Äôm very lucky and honored to have you along side me for this ride. I can‚Äôt wait to share a picture of a smooth road with blue skies when we‚Äôre feeling the success to come!\n\n194#My newest partner in crime|John, you have only been in Workhuman for a few weeks and I am already feeling the impact you are making from across the pond. There is so many employment branding initiatives launched, being planned and prioritized and you have been more than happy to get  stuck right in. You are super responsive and eager to help. I am so excited to  be partnering with you on these many many future EB projects.\n\n195#Working with the moving parts|Thanks for going out to lunch with me to give insight on how you work and helping me see how we can work better as a team. Thanks for listening to my thoughts and for putting up with my run-on sentences!\n\n196#Super Fast Response|Thank you all so much for dropping everything to help out with this important request from Unilever. It came directly from the top and is for a key meeting with Unilever's new CEO. Recognition is very much on their agenda and the creative work you pulled together within a matter of hours, will be used to illustrate the global direction they are taking. The VP Global Reward specifically requested that I pass on her sincere appreciation for the work you've done on this. THANK YOU!!\n\n197#Happy Monthiversary|John! You made it through your first month. Kudos to you for participating in a team offsite on day 3, when you hadn't even met most of the team yet! This recognition is under Respect for All. You have been proactive in meeting/greeting/learning from not just the people in the agency, but you've gone beyond to meet and learn from many others on the marketing team. Critical in  understanding the big picture to shape the resources we need. Bonus that you are a Workfront pro.